The '''2015 ANZ Championship season''' was the eighth season of the [[ANZ Championship]], which commenced on 28 February. The 2015 season started earlier than previous seasons, to accommodate the [[2015 Netball World Cup]] in August. The season comprised 69 matches, including an initial 14-week round-robin stage, followed by a finals series. The 2015 season featured two ANZAC Day matches, Friday night matches, a new venue and a new host city.<ref>{{cite web|title=2015 ANZ Championship Draw Released|url=http://www.anz-championship.com/News/Latest-News/ArtMID/1500/ArticleID/2692/2015-ANZ-Championship-draw-released|website=ANZ Championship}}</ref>

== Overview ==

=== Format ===

The ANZ Championship is played over 17 weeks, comprising 14 "Regular Rounds", followed by Conference Finals and the ANZ Championship Finals Series. Matches are generally played on Saturdays, Sundays and Mondays.

Each team competes in 13 regular matches. Australian teams play all other Australian teams twice, and New Zealand teams once; New Zealand teams play all other New Zealand teams twice, and Australian teams once. <ref>http://www.anz-championship.com/About-Us/League-Format</ref>

