{{Refimprove|date=February 2017}} {{Infobox stadium | stadium_name = Keine Sorgen EisArena | image = [[File:Linzer_Eissporthalle.jpg|250px|Linzer Eissporthalle]] | location = Untere Donaulände 11, 4020 [[Linz]] | coordinates = | broke_ground = | opened = 1986 | owner = | operator = | construction_cost = | architect = | former_names = Donauhalle | tenants =[[EHC Black Wings Linz]] ([[Erste Bank Hockey League|EBEL]]) | seating_capacity = 4,863 }} '''Keine Sorgen EisArena''' is an [[indoor arena|indoor sporting arena]] located in [[Linz]], [[Austria]]. The '''Donauhalle''' has been called the "Keine Sorgen EisArena" since 2008 as a result of a sponsorship deal with an Austrian insurance group. The arena has a capacity of 4,863 people,<ref name=arena>nachrichten.at, [http://www.nachrichten.at/sport/black_wings/Fast-5000-Fans-werden-die-Eishalle-zum-Kochen-bringen;art107,1521821 Fast 5000 Fans werden die Eishalle zum Kochen bringen]</ref> with around 1,000 seats and was built in 1986. It is currently home of the [[EHC Black Wings Linz]] [[ice hockey]] team.
'''Donauhalle''' also refers to an exhibition complex in [[Ulm]], [[Germany]].
