{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2014}} {{Use British English|date=March 2014}} {{Infobox football tournament | logo = | founded = 1877 | number of teams = | region = [[Shropshire]] | other regions = [[File:Flag_of_Powys.svg|border|25px]] | current champions = [[Shawbury United F.C.|Shawbury United]] | most successful club = [[Shrewsbury Town]] (66 cups) | website = | broadcasters = | current = }} The '''Shropshire Senior Cup''' is a county cup [[football (soccer)|football]] competition that is open for professional and non-professional senior football teams in the [[England|English]] county of [[Shropshire]].
The competition is one of the oldest cup competitions in the world, and notably, the original winning trophy is still presented to the winners, some 130 years after the Cup's inception. It is organised by the [[Shropshire Football Association]] and is annual.
The competition was first staged in the [[1877-78 in English football|1877–78]] season, the inaugural winners being Shrewsbury F.C, who beat Wellington Parish Church Institute 1–0. (Shrewsbury F.C are not connected to the current [[Shrewsbury Town F.C.|Shrewsbury Town]], and dissolved late in 1879.)
Over the years, the competition has been dominated by the county's two leading football teams, Shrewsbury Town and [[Telford United F.C.|Telford United]], and more recently [[A.F.C. Telford United]] following the demise of the old Telford United in 2004.
Other county teams to have featured in the cup in recent years have included [[Market Drayton Town F.C.|Market Drayton Town]], [[Shifnal Town F.C.|Shifnal Town]], [[Bridgnorth Town F.C.|Bridgnorth Town]], [[Ludlow Town F.C.|Ludlow Town]] and [[The New Saints F.C.|The New Saints]].
