'''Somerset Cricket Club Trojans''' is a [[Bermuda|Bermudian]] [[association football|football]] club who participate in the [[Bermudian Premier Division]]. They are based in [[Somerset, Bermuda|Somerset]], [[Bermuda]].

==History==
Trojans were formed in 1964 after a merger between ''West End Rovers'' and 2nd division ''Somerset Colts''. Rovers were founded as ''West End SC'' in the 1930s.<ref>[http://www.rsssf.com/tablesb/bermfound.html Bermuda - List of Foundation Dates] - RSSSF</ref> They are Bermuda's most successful team, winning the league a record 10 times.<ref>[http://www.rsssf.com/tablesb/bermchamp.html Bermuda - List of Champions] - RSSSF</ref>

In April 2015, Trojans won their first league title in 22 years and their tenth in total after beating [[Southampton Rangers]] 3-0.<ref>[http://www.royalgazette.com/article/20150401/SPORT01/150409985 Trojans end their title drought] - Royal Gazette</ref>

==Achievements==
*'''[[Bermudian Premier Division]]: 10'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesb/bermchamp.html|title=Bermuda - List of Champions|accessdate=8 February 2015}}</ref>
:: 1966–67, 1967–68, 1968–69, 1969–70, 1981–82, 1982–83, 1983–84, 1986–87, 1992–93, 2014-15

*'''[[Bermuda FA Cup]]: 9'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesb/bermcuphist.html|title=Bermuda - List of Cup Winners|accessdate=8 February 2015}}</ref>
:: 1967–68, 1968–69, 1969–70, 1971–72, 1975–76, 1976–77, 1978–79, 1987–88, 1989–90

